legacy.full_text:
It's #CervicalCancer Awareness Month!

Cervical cancer could be the first cancer EVER in the world to be eliminated, if

9⃣0⃣% of girls are vaccinated
7⃣0⃣% of women are screened
9⃣0⃣% of women with cervical disease receive treatment

 https://t.co/Ewsm6jN0UT

¡Es el Mes de la Concienciación sobre el #Cancerdecuellodeutero!
 El cáncer de cuello uterino podría ser el primer cáncer del mundo en ser eliminado, si
 9⃣0⃣% de niñas vacunadas
 7⃣0⃣% de mujeres se someten a cribado
 9⃣0⃣% de mujeres con enfermedad cervical reciben tratamiento

Vaccines can protect you from serious illness and death from #COVID19. But #DYK that after being vaccinated, you should STILL

😷 #WearAMask
↔️ Keep a safe distance
🪟 Open windows
🤧 Cough/sneeze into your elbow
👐 Keep hands clean

to protect others❓ Here’s why ⬇

Everyone has a role to play in stopping #AntimicrobialResistance (AMR).
 
Join WHO to spread awareness, stop resistance by adding blue 🔵🔵🔵 on your social media during World Antimicrobial Awareness Week 18-24 November.
 
More info 👉https://t.co/9TDeiZ39ps https://t.co/4nPbJF1iDv

Without effective antimicrobials, the success of modern medicine in treating infections, including during major surgery and cancer chemotherapy, would be at increased risk. We all have a role and responsibility to do all we can to #StopDrugResistance. https://t.co/kueLPSthV4
